com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain

Interface DefaultResponseHandler<T,E>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object that is returned to you in the onSuccess method.
    E - Tye type of error that is returned to you in the reportErrorBackToApplication method.

    public interface DefaultResponseHandler<T,E>
    This is the base response handler for SDK async responses. When making an SDK call that requires an async response you'll provide one of these to discover the call's eventual success or failure.

    A successful response will result in onSuccess being called.

    A failed response will result in reportErrorBackToApplication being called.

      • onError

        void onError(E error)
        This method indicates that an error occurred while trying to satisfy the request. An Error object is returned back, that would contain more details are the error that occurred, providing information such as error code, error message etc, thus helping the clients to fix the same. SDK errors are represented with the PPError<> class.
        Parameters:
        error - - an object that contains more detailed error information.
